 <td>2nd</td>\n      <td>No penalty</td>\n      <td>2% (or no penalty if you owe less than £400)</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>3rd</td>\n      <td>2% (or no penalty if you owe less than £400)</td>\n      <td>5% (or no penalty if you owe less than £400)</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>4th</td>\n      <td>5% (or no penalty if you owe less than £400)</td>\n      <td>10%</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>5th</td>\n      <td>10%</td>\n      <td>15%</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>6 or more</td>\n      <td>15%</td>\n      <td>15%</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h3>Exceptions</h3>\n\n<p>There’s no penalty if you send a late <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> Return and you have no tax to pay or you’re due a <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> repayment. </p>\n\n<h2>Penalties for incorrect <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> Returns</h2>\n\n<p>If your <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> Return is inaccurate <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> can charge you a penalty (between 15% and 100% of the unpaid owed). </p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/about/new-penalties/new-penalties.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Penalties for inaccurate tax returns' (PDF, 200KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Penalties for inaccurate tax returns’ (PDF, 200KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Interest</h2>\n\n<p>You may be charged interest on any tax you owe.</p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/vat-returns/assessments","slug":"assessments","order":7,"title":"Assessments","body":"<p>HM Revenue &amp; Customs (<abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>) can send you a <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> &lsquo;assessment&rsquo; for example: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>if you&rsquo;re late with a <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> Return </li>\n  <li>your <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> Return has an error on it </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The assessment will explain why <abbr titl