line</a> - including partnerships and a group of companies registering under one <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> number.</p>\n\n<p>By doing this you&rsquo;ll register for <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> and create a <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> online account (sometimes known as a &lsquo;Government Gateway account&rsquo;). You need this to send your <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> Returns to <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>. </p>\n\n<p>If an agent registers you for <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr>, you must <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://online.hmrc.gov.uk/registration/organisation\" title=\"Sign up for a VAT online account\">sign up for a <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> online account separately</a> (select option ‘<abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> submit returns’). You can only do this <strong>after</strong> <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> sends your <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> number to you.</p>\n\n<h2>When you can’t register online</h2>\n\n<p>You must <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/vat/start/register/how-to-register.htm\" title=\"Registering for VAT by post\">register by post</a> if:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you want to apply for a ‘<a href=\"/vat-registration/when-to-register\" title=\"Exceptions to compulsory VAT registration\">registration exception</a>’ </li>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re an EU business ‘distance selling’ to the UK </li>\n  <li>you import (‘acquire’) goods from another EU country </li>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re registering for <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> and joining the Agricultural Flat Rate Scheme</li>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re registering the divisions or business units of a body corporate under separate <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> numbers</li>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re disposing of assets on which 8th or 13th Directive refunds have been claimed</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If you register by post, y